data.description: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

data.name: gigalith
data.description: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

data.name: woobat
data.description: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

data.name: swoobat
data.description: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

data.name: drilbur
data.description: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

data.name: excadrill
data.description: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

data.name: audino
data.description: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

data.name: timburr
data.description: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

data.name: gurdurr
data.description: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

data.name: conkeldurr
data.description: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

data.name: tympole
data.description: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

data.name: palpitoad
data.description: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

data.name: seismitoad
data.description: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

data.name: throh
data.description: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

data.name: sawk
data.description: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

data.name: sewaddle
data.description: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

data.name: swadloon
data.description: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

data.name: leavanny
data.description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

data.name: venipede
data.description: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

data.name: whirlipede
data.description: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

data.name: scolipede
data.description: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

data.name: cottonee
data.description: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

data.name: whimsicott
data.description: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

data.name: petilil
data.description: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

data.name: lilligant
data.description: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

data.name: sandile
data.description: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

data.name: krokorok
data.description: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

data.name: krookodile
data.description: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

data.name: darumaka
data.description: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

data.name: maractus
data.description: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

data.name: dwebble
data.description: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

data.name: crustle
data.description: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

data.name: scraggy
data.description: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

data.name: scrafty
data.description: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

data.name: sigilyph
data.description: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

data.name: yamask
data.description: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

data.name: cofagrigus
data.description: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

data.name: tirtouga
data.description: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

data.name: carracosta
data.description: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

data.name: archen
data.description: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

data.name: archeops
data.description: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

data.name: trubbish
data.description: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

data.name: garbodor
data.description: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

data.name: zorua
data.description: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

data.name: zoroark
data.description: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

data.name: minccino
data.description: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

data.name: cinccino
data.description: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

data.name: gothita
data.description: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

data.name: gothorita
data.description: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

data.name: gothitelle
data.description: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

data.name: solosis
data.description: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

data.name: duosion
data.description: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

data.name: reuniclus
data.description: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

data.name: ducklett
data.description: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

data.name: swanna
data.description: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

data.name: vanillite
data.description: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

data.name: vanillish
data.description: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

data.name: vanilluxe
data.description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

data.name: deerling
data.description: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

data.name: sawsbuck
data.description: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

data.name: emolga
data.description: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

data.name: karrablast
data.description: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

data.name: escavalier
data.description: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

data.name: foongus
data.description: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

data.name: amoonguss
data.description: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

data.name: frillish
data.description: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

data.name: jellicent
data.description: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

data.name: alomomola
data.description: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

data.name: joltik
data.description: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

data.name: galvantula
data.description: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

data.name: ferroseed
data.description: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

data.name: ferrothorn
data.description: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

data.name: klink
data.description: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

data.name: klang
data.description: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

data.name: klinklang
data.description: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

data.name: tynamo
data.description: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

data.name: eelektrik
data.description: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

data.name: eelektross
data.description: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

data.name: elgyem
data.description: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

data.name: beheeyem
data.description: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

data.name: litwick
data.description: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

data.name: lampent
data.description: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

data.name: chandelure
data.description: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

data.name: axew
data.description: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

data.name: fraxure
data.description: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

data.name: haxorus
data.description: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

data.name: cubchoo
data.description: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

data.name: beartic
data.description: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

data.name: cryogonal
data.description: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

data.name: shelmet
data.description: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

data.name: accelgor
data.description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

data.name: stunfisk
data.description: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

data.name: mienfoo
data.description: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

data.name: mienshao
data.description: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

data.name: druddigon
data.description: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

data.name: golett
data.description: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

data.name: golurk
data.description: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

data.name: pawniard
data.description: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

data.name: bisharp
data.description: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

data.name: bouffalant
data.description: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

data.name: rufflet
data.description: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

data.name: braviary
data.description: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

data.name: vullaby
data.description: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

data.name: mandibuzz
data.description: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

data.name: heatmor
data.description: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

data.name: durant
data.description: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

data.name: deino
data.description: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

data.name: zweilous
data.description: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

data.name: hydreigon
data.description: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

data.name: larvesta
data.description: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

data.name: volcarona
data.description: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

data.name: cobalion
data.description: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

data.name: terrakion
data.description: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

data.name: virizion
data.description: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

data.name: reshiram
data.description: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

data.name: zekrom
data.description: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

data.name: kyurem
data.description: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: genesect
data.description: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

data.name: chespin
data.description: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

data.name: quilladin
data.description: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

data.name: chesnaught
data.description: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

data.name: fennekin
data.description: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: braixen
data.description: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

data.name: delphox
data.description: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

data.name: froakie
data.description: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

data.name: frogadier
data.description: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

data.name: greninja
data.description: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

data.name: bunnelby
data.description: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

data.name: diggersby
data.description: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

data.name: fletchling
data.description: These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

data.name: fletchinder
data.description: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

data.name: talonflame
data.description: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

data.name: scatterbug
data.description: When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

data.name: spewpa
data.description: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

data.name: vivillon
data.description: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

data.name: litleo
data.description: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

data.name: pyroar
data.description: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

data.name: flabebe
data.description: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.

data.name: floette
data.description: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

data.name: florges
data.description: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

data.name: skiddo
data.description: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

data.name: gogoat
data.description: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

data.name: pancham
data.description: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

data.name: pangoro
data.description: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

data.name: furfrou
data.description: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

data.name: espurr
data.description: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

data.name: honedge
data.description: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

data.name: doublade
data.description: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

data.name: spritzee
data.description: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

data.name: aromatisse
data.description: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

data.name: swirlix
data.description: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

data.name: slurpuff
data.description: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

data.name: inkay
data.description: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

data.name: malamar
data.description: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

data.name: binacle
data.description: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

data.name: barbaracle
data.description: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

data.name: skrelp
data.description: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

data.name: dragalge
data.description: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

data.name: clauncher
data.description: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

data.name: clawitzer
data.description: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

data.name: helioptile
data.description: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

data.name: heliolisk
data.description: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

data.name: tyrunt
data.description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

data.name: tyrantrum
data.description: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

data.name: amaura
data.description: This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

data.name: aurorus
data.description: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

data.name: sylveon
data.description: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

data.name: hawlucha
data.description: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

data.name: dedenne
data.description: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

data.name: carbink
data.description: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

data.name: goomy
data.description: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.

data.name: sliggoo
data.description: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.

data.name: goodra
data.description: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

data.name: klefki
data.description: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

data.name: phantump
data.description: These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

data.name: trevenant
data.description: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

data.name: bergmite
data.description: It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

data.name: avalugg
data.description: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

data.name: noibat
data.description: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

data.name: noivern
data.description: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

data.name: xerneas
data.description: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

data.name: yveltal
data.description: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

data.name: diancie
data.description: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

data.name: volcanion
data.description: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.
